## elf related tool
    * nm
        * list symbols from obj files
    * objdump
        * display information from obj files
    * readelf
        * display information about ELF files
    * ldd
        * print shared obj dependencies

## network related tool
    * < web perf tool >
        * siege
            * web perf tool, like ab
        * ab

    * < traffic tool >
        * hping3
        * curl
        * scapy
 
    * < sniffer >
        * ngrep
            * search and filter network packets
        * tcpdump
        * tshark
        * tcprewrite
        * tcpreplay
        * editcap
            * Edit and/or translate the format of capture files

    * < config >
        * ethtool

    * < display >
        * lsof
        * netstat
        * ss
            * display sockets' status
        * mtr
            * replace ping and traceroute
        * iftop
            * see network traffic
        * iptraf
            * see network traffic

## every linux networking tool I know -- Julia Evans
* ss, netstat, lsof, fuser
    * check open port
* tc
* rsync
    * copy only changed files over ssh
* ngrep
* tshark
* tcpflow
    * capture and assemble TCP streams
* mitmproxy
    * spy on SSL connections your programs are making
* p0f
    * idenify OS of hosts connecting to you
* openvpn
* wiregurad
    * a newer vpn
* socat
    * proxy a TCP socket to a unix domain socket
* nftables
    * a new version of iptables
* mtr
    * a better traceroute
* tcptraceroute
    * using tcp packets instead of icmp to tracroute
* ethtool
    * manage physical ethernet connections and networks cards
* iw, iwconfig
    * manage wireless networks settings
* sysctl
    * config linux kernel's network stack

* openssl
    * do literally anything with SSL certifacates
* stunnel
    * make a SSL proxy for an insecure servere
* iptraf, nethogs, iftop, ntop
    * see what's using bandwidth
* ab, nload, iperf
    * benchmarking tools
* python -m SimpleHTTPServer
    * serve files from a directory
* ipcalc
    * easily see what 12.21.2.3/25 means
* nsenter
    * enter a container process's network namespace

### http

* httpie
